<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;</span><span class="s0">EXPERIMENTAL!</span><span class="s1">&lt;/strong&gt;</span><span class="s0">: This API may change or disappear in later pygame releases. If</span>
<span class="s0">you use this, your code may break with the next pygame release.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">The pygame package does not import gfxdraw automatically when loaded, so it</span>
<span class="s0">must imported explicitly to be used.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;highlight-default notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;highlight&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;kn&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">import</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;nn&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;kn&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">import</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;nn&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.gfxdraw</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">For all functions the arguments are strictly positional and integers are</span>
<span class="s0">accepted for coordinates and radii. The </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">color</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">argument can be one of the</span>
<span class="s0">following formats:</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;blockquote&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;simple&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">a </span><span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;color.html#pygame.Color&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;xref py py-mod docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.Color</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip-content&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame object for color representations</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; </span><span class="s0">object</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">See the </span><span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;draw.html#module-pygame.draw&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;xref py py-mod docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.draw</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip-content&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame module for drawing shapes</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; </span><span class="s0">module for alternative draw methods.</span>
<span class="s0">The </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.gfxdraw</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">module differs from the </span><span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;draw.html#module-pygame.draw&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;xref py py-mod docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.draw</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip-content&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame module for drawing shapes</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; </span><span class="s0">module in</span>
<span class="s0">the API it uses and the different draw functions available.</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.gfxdraw</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">wraps the primitives from the library called SDL_gfx,</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Draws an arc on the given surface. For an arc with its endpoints connected</span>
<span class="s0">to its center use </span><span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;#pygame.gfxdraw.pie&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pygame.gfxdraw.pie&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;xref py py-meth docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pie()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</span><span class="s0">.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">The two angle arguments are given in degrees and indicate the start and stop</span>
<span class="s0">positions of the arc. The arc is drawn in a clockwise direction from the</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">start_angle</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">to the </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">stop_angle</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">. If </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">start_angle</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">==</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">stop_angle</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">,</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;sig-prename descclassname&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.gfxdraw.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;sig-name descname&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pie</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;sig-paren&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">(</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;sig-paren&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">)</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;headerlink&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;#pygame.gfxdraw.pie&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;Permalink to this definition&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0"></span><span class="s1">&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/dt&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;dd&gt;&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line-block&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;summaryline&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">draw a pie</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;signature&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pie(surface, x, y, r, start_angle, stop_angle, color) -</span><span class="s4">&amp;gt; </span><span class="s0">None</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Draws an unfilled pie on the given surface. A pie is an </span><span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;#pygame.gfxdraw.arc&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pygame.gfxdraw.arc&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;xref py py-meth docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">arc()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; </span><span class="s0">with its</span>
<span class="s0">endpoints connected to its center.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">The two angle arguments are given in degrees and indicate the start and stop</span>
<span class="s0">positions of the pie. The pie is drawn in a clockwise direction from the</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">start_angle</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">to the </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">stop_angle</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">. If </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">start_angle</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">==</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">stop_angle</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">,</span>
<span class="s0">a straight line will be drawn from the center position at the given angle,</span>
<span class="s0">to a length of the radius.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;dl </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;field-list simple&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;dt </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;sig sig-object py title&quot; </span><span class="s2">id</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pygame.gfxdraw.textured_polygon&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;sig-prename descclassname&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.gfxdraw.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;sig-name descname&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">textured_polygon</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;sig-paren&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">(</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;sig-paren&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">)</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;headerlink&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;#pygame.gfxdraw.textured_polygon&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;Permalink to this definition&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0"></span><span class="s1">&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/dt&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;dd&gt;&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line-block&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;summaryline&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">draw a textured polygon</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;signature&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">textured_polygon(surface, points, texture, tx, ty) -</span><span class="s4">&amp;gt; </span><span class="s0">None</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Draws a textured polygon on the given surface. For better performance, the</span>
<span class="s0">surface and the texture should have the same format.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">A per-pixel alpha texture blit to a per-pixel alpha surface will differ from</span>
<span class="s0">a </span><span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;surface.html#pygame.Surface.blit&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;xref py py-func docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.Surface.blit()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip-content&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">draw one image onto another</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; </span><span class="s0">blit. Also, a per-pixel alpha texture cannot be</span>
<span class="s0">used with an 8-bit per pixel destination.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">The adjacent coordinates in the </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">points</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">argument, as well as the first</span>
<span class="s0">and last points, will be connected by line segments.</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;</span><span class="s0">color</span><span class="s1">&lt;/strong&gt; </span><span class="s0">(</span><span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;color.html#pygame.Color&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pygame.Color&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;em&gt;</span><span class="s0">Color</span><span class="s1">&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; </span><span class="s0">or </span><span class="s1">&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;</span><span class="s0">tuple</span><span class="s1">&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;</span><span class="s0">(</span><span class="s1">&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;</span><span class="s0">int</span><span class="s1">&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;</span><span class="s0">int</span><span class="s1">&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;</span><span class="s0">int</span><span class="s1">&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;</span><span class="s0">, </span><span class="s1">&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;</span><span class="s0">[</span><span class="s1">&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;</span><span class="s0">int</span><span class="s1">&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;</span><span class="s0">]</span><span class="s1">&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;</span><span class="s0">)</span><span class="s1">&lt;/em&gt;</span><span class="s0">) -- color to draw with, the alpha value is optional if using a</span>
<span class="s0">tuple </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">(RGB[A])</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/ul&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/dd&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;dt </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;field-even&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Returns</span><span class="s1">&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;colon&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">:</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/dt&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;dd </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;field-even&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">None</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;dt </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;field-odd&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Return type</span><span class="s1">&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;colon&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">:</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/dt&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;dd </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;field-odd&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">NoneType</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;dt </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;field-even&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Raises</span><span class="s1">&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;colon&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">:</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/dt&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;dd </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;field-even&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;ul </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;simple&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;</span><span class="s0">ValueError</span><span class="s1">&lt;/strong&gt; </span><span class="s0">-- if </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">steps</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s4">&amp;lt;</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">2</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;</span><span class="s0">ValueError</span><span class="s1">&lt;/strong&gt; </span><span class="s0">-- if </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">len(points)</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s4">&amp;lt;</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">3</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">(must have at least 3 points)</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</span>
